explanation: The code used print(num_set.pop, flush=True) which prints the pop method object instead of calling it. As a result no element was removed or printed. I fixed it by calling pop() — print(num_set.pop(), flush=True) — so an element is returned, removed from the set, and printed.
fixed_code:
N = int(input())
num_set = set(range(1, 2*N+2))
while True:
    print(num_set.pop(), flush=True)
    
    a = int(input()) #aは青木君が宣言した数
    if a==0:
        break
    num_set.discard(a)
